OL,3,CCost of living tops parents' fears for
OL,4,Cchildren's futures ` study
OL,6,FThe cost of living is continuing to
OL,7,Ftop parents' fears for their
OL,8,Fchildren's futures ` while future
OL,9,Fpandemics and global instability are
OL,10,Fof little concern, an annual survey
OL,11,Fsuggests.
OL,13,FTwo in five parents (42%) said the
OL,14,Fcost of living was their top fear for
OL,15,Ftheir children's future, up from 37%
OL,16,Flast year, according to Wealthify's
OL,17,F'Hopes and Fears' research.
OL,19,FThis was followed by mental health
OL,20,F(37%), social issues and bullying
OL,21,F(28%) and social media (28%).
