OL,3,CCost of living tops parents' fears for
OL,4,Cchildren's futures ` study
OL,6,FThe cost of living was also the most
OL,7,Fcommon fear for the future among 16 to
OL,8,F18-year-olds (45%), followed by
OL,9,Fworries about mental health (32%).
OL,11,FFears associated with climate change
OL,12,Fwere of more concern for parents (24%)
OL,13,Fthan teenagers (16%), while levels of
OL,14,Fworry about social issues or bullying
OL,15,F(8%) and social media (10%) were also
OL,16,Fmuch lower among youngsters than their
OL,17,Fparents.
