OL,3,CCost of living tops parents' fears for
OL,4,Cchildren's futures ` study
OL,6,FGlobal instability and war also do not
OL,7,Fmake the top 10 concerns, with just
OL,8,F15% of parents citing it as a concern
OL,9,Ffor their children's future ` similar
OL,10,Fto last year's figure of 12% ` and
OL,11,Fonly 12% of 16 to 18-year-olds naming
OL,12,Fit as a major worry.
OL,14,FTeenagers are more likely to cite not
OL,15,Fbeing able to buy a house (36%), or
OL,16,Ftheir savings and finances (42%), as
OL,17,Fmajor fears for their futures, while
OL,18,Fjust a quarter of parents (26%) raised
OL,19,Fthe ability to buy a house or build
OL,20,Fsavings and finances as a major fear
OL,21,Ffor their children's futures.
